OL,7,FMr Smith said: "It seems that when
OL,8,Fthey met, having taken (the
OL,9,Fdefendant's) cash, Mr Johnson went
OL,10,Fback on his side of the deal and
OL,11,Fsimply rode off. In short, he took the
OL,12,Fmoney and ran."
OL,14,FThe prosecutor said the defendant was
OL,15,Fleft feeling "pretty foolish, pretty
OL,16,Fembarrassed and, no doubt, pretty
OL,17,Fangry."
OL,19,FHe told jurors: "But whatever Mr
OL,20,FJohnson had done, you may feel, he
OL,21,Fdidn't deserve what happened next."
